VST01 Table 1 (Default) Vital Sign Results and change from Baseline By Visit Table 1.

vst01_1.Rd

The VST01 table provides an overview of the Vital Sign values and its change from baseline of each respective arm over the course of the trial.

Usage

vst01_1_main(
  adam_db,
  armvar = "ACTARM",
  summaryvars = c(`Value at Visit` = "AVAL", `Change from \nBaseline` = "CHG"),
  visitvar = "AVISIT",
  deco = std_deco("VST01"),
  ...
)

vst01_1_lyt(
  armvar,
  summaryvars,
  summaryvars_lbls,
  visitvar,
  lbl_avisit,
  lbl_param,
  deco,
  ...
)

vst01_1_pre(adam_db, ...)

vst01_1_post(tlg, prune_0 = TRUE, ...)

vst01_1

Format

An object of class chevron_t of length 1.

Arguments

adam_db

(dm) object containing the ADaM datasets

armvar

(character) variable used for column splitting

summaryvars

(vector of character) the variables to be analyzed. For this table, AVAL and CHG by default.

visitvar

(character) typically one of "AVISIT" (Default) or "ATPTN" depending on the type of time point to be displayed.

deco

(character) decoration with title, subtitles and main_footer content

...

not used.

summaryvars_lbls

(vector of character) the label of the variables to be analyzed.

lbl_avisit

(character) label of the visitvar variable.

lbl_param

(character) label of the PARAM variable.

tlg

(TableTree, Listing or ggplot) object typically produced by a main function.

prune_0

(logical) remove 0 count rows

Details

  • The Analysis Value column, displays the number of patients, the mean, standard deviation, median and range of the analysis value for each visit.

  • The Change from Baseline column, displays the number of patient and the mean, standard deviation, median and range of changes relative to the baseline.

  • Remove zero-count rows unless overridden with prune_0 = FALSE.

  • Split columns by arm, typically ACTARM.

  • Does not include a total column by default.

  • Sorted based on factor level; first by PARAM labels in alphabetic order then by chronological time point given by AVISIT. Re-level to customize order

Functions

  • vst01_1_main(): Main TLG function

  • vst01_1_lyt(): Layout

  • vst01_1_pre(): Preprocessing

  • vst01_1_post(): Postprocessing

Note

  • adam_db object must contain an advs table with the columns specified in summaryvars.
